gomodel:SYNGO_229  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This paper demonstrates localization of drebrin A in dendritic spines in the cerebral cortex using confocal and electron microscopy (figures 3,4, 5). This paper also presents data that Drebrin A co-sediments with other actin-binding proteins in the insoluble fraction (figure 6). And, immuno-EM labeling on synaptosomes showed Drebrin A labeling on filamentous materials that were associated with postsynaptic densities (figure 7). Finally, biochemical evidence is provided that drebrin interacts with actin and the actin-binding proteins gelsolin and myosin II (figure 8). Together these data indicate that Drebrin A is bound to the postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton.. Experimental description: from M&M: \"Ten-week-old Wistar rats were perfused with 4% paraformaldehyde in 0.1 m phosphate buffer, pH 7.2.[.,..]\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_229" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

